    "guide.step1.history.note": "This helps determine whether keto is appropriate for you, or whether a gentler low-carb or Mediterranean-style approach might be safer.",
    "guide.step1.meds": "Review Medications",
    "guide.step1.meds.desc": "A ketogenic diet can change how your body responds to several drugs, especially:",
    "guide.step1.meds.list1": "Diabetes medications (insulin, sulfonylureas, SGLT2 inhibitors)",
    "guide.step1.meds.list2": "Blood pressure medications (you may need lower doses as weight and BP improve)",
    "guide.step1.meds.list3": "Diuretics and certain psychiatric or neurological medications",
    "guide.step1.meds.action1": "Adjust insulin doses before or shortly after you start",
    "guide.step1.meds.action2": "Reduce or change blood pressure meds to avoid dizziness or fainting",
